  <annotation>Jens Peter's storytelling provides a map for reading features of the local landscape, instilling significance in features that others might not notice. In this manner, Jens Peter emerges as a knowledgeable guide to local topography, and provides a reading of the landscape that infuses it with tragedy and danger. The loss of the local minister in a horrible accident would have been a memorable event. 

     It is about five kilometers from Vrejlev to Hvidstedg&#xE5;rd, and one can easily imagine a shortcut over the meadow between the road from Vrejlev to T&#xE5;rs, across Boller k&#xE6;r (marsh), and on through the meadow at Hvidstedg&#xE5;rd.

     In the published version of the story, Tang Kristensen reversed the order of several sentences for no apparent reason. He also mistranscribed the name of the farm as Hvilstedg&#xE5;rd. The meadow near Hvidstedg&#xE5;rd is fed by the Uggerby river.</annotation>
  <danish_manuscript>I Hvidstedgaards Enge er der et sv&#xE6;re
stort Hul de kalder Pr&#xE6;stehullet den Dag
i Dag er. Der kj&#xF8;rte en Pr&#xE6;st fra Vrej
lev i paa Isen baade med Sl&#xE6;de og
Kusk og det hele blev v&#xE6;k. Det er
nu groet sammen og er ikke n&#xE6;r s. stort
som f&#xF8;r.</danish_manuscript>
  <english_manuscript>In Hvidstedg&#xE5;rd's meadows, there is a really big hole, they called it Minister Hole to this very day. A minister from Vrejlev drove onto the ice and into it with his sleigh and driver and everything disappeared. It has grown in a bit and isn't nearly as big as it was before.</english_manuscript>
  <danish_publication>I Hvilstedg&#xE5;rds enge er der et sv&#xE6;re stort hul, de kalder Pr&#xE6;steh&#xF8;llet den dag i dag er. Men det er groet meget sammen og ikke n&#xE6;r s&#xE5; stort som f&#xF6;r. Her kj&#xF8;rte en pr&#xE6;st fra Vrejlev i p&#xE5; isen b&#xE5;de med sl&#xE6;de og kusk og det hele, og der blev det.</danish_publication>
  <english_publication>In Hvilstedg&#xE5;rd&#x2019;s meadows, there is a really big hole, they called it the Minister Hole to this very day. It has grown in a bit and isn&#x2019;t nearly as big as it was before. A minister from Vrejlev drove onto the ice and into it with his sleigh and driver and everything, and they stayed there.</english_publication>
